summary: i didnt think much about this
title: i didnt think much about this
body:
lowercase intended cos im typing on the bed

peter is sold for auction and catches tony’s eyes immediately. the bidding starts at 5 million and ends at 1 billion as tony really wanted to have this boy. maybe it was too much, creating a 500 million gap when they reached 500 million. peter never thought that he was worth so much. he was just a toy after all, from a poor family and abandoned town. 

peter was given to tony after the auction and tony is very much pleased, not a single feeling of regret washed over him. he knew that this boy was going to be worth every penny. he didnt care about the money though, he was a multi billionaire who owned millions of companies around the whole world. the moment they got home that night, peter was escorted to his room. which he expected to be a dungeon. boy was he wrong.

he was pushed into a beautifully furnished room. the ceiling was high, there was a fireplace, the walls were a beautiful velvet and the bed was huge. across the room was a door that was actually a closet, full of clothes from prada, gucci, louis vuitton, you name it, its there. 

peter was in complete awe. was this his room? or was it stark’s? he doubted it though, the room looked kind of feminine and mr. stark…? there’s nothing feminine about that guy. before confirming anything, peter just sat on the fluffy bed and took a deep breath. whatever that was going to happen to him, its out of his control; he doesnt own his own self anymore. 

2 knocks were heard before the door opened. there stood a tall man, it was tony stark, the man who bought peter. “master,” peter called and stood up. “ease, boy. im not doing anything to you, yet.” tony gestured and peter sat down again. peter suddenly felt uneasy, he looked at tony, viewed his profile. he wore a blue suit that peter was sure that cost a quarter of a million. tony’s body was fairly built, his eyes were a dark hazel, his hair was black but the roots were starting to turn white. he wore a few rings, a rolex watch was around his wrist and?? well, he was kinda handsome. kinda. 

“whats your name? tony asked peter and peter pursed his lips. “dont be afraid of me,” tony sighs and walked into the room’s bath. he turned on the faucets and filled the tub with warm water. “youre tired, arent you? go take a bath first. lets talk tomorrow morning.”

peter was about to speak but tony already left the room. “im peter…” he said, looking at the door. he felt unsure about the day that was about to come but one thing he was sure about was that he needed to prepare himself for it.
